than ever before. Creative chaos on all sides? Not really.Denis Hänzi investigates how old ideals and new realities in the German-language theatrical landscape are deriving from the interplay between individual working methods and institutional configurations. Extrapolating on Bourdieu's concept of habitus/field, he develops a theory of charisma which provides an innovative approach to the analysis of contemporary artistic worlds. That the »order of the theater« bears visible traits of a culture of success which appears to consolidate the male dominance in directing is just one of the illuminating findings that makes this book fascinating for theater-makers and theater-goers alike.  afunded by OAPEN-CH-SNF  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBourdieu. 4aCharisma. 4aFeld. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aHabitus. 4aKultursoziologie. 4aKunst. 4aTheater. 4aTheaterregie. 4aTheaterwissenschaft. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aArts.  aGender Studies.  aSociology of Culture.  aTheatre Studies.  aTheatre.2 aOAPEN-CH-SNFefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013z978311102523008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2013z9783110401219oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383762342040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839423424?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839423424zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839423424/original  a978-3-11-102523-0 transcript Backlist